I cannot render a 3D model directly in this chat interface. However, I can provide you with the **complete code** to generate a 3D house using Python and the `trimesh` library.

You can run this code on your local machine to instantly visualize a 3D house.

### Prerequisites
You will need to install the `trimesh` library:
```bash
pip install trimesh
```

### Python Code to Generate a 3D House
This script creates a simple house geometry (a cube for the body and a pyramid for the roof) and saves it as an `.obj` file, which can be opened in Blender, Maya, or any 3D viewer.

```python
import trimesh
import numpy as np

def create_house():
    # 1. Define the House Body (Cube)
    # Dimensions: Width=10, Height=8, Depth=10
    body = trimesh.creation.box(extents=[10, 8, 10])

    # 2. Define the Roof (Pyramid)
    # We create a pyramid with a square base
    roof = trimesh.creation.pyramid(
        base_extents=[10, 10], 
        height=4, 
        sections=4  # Number of sides (4 for a square pyramid)
    )

    # 3. Position the Roof on top of the Body
    # Move the roof up by half the body height (4) and shift it slightly to align
    roof.apply_translation([0, 4, 0])

    # 4. Combine the meshes
    house = trimesh.util.concatenate([body, roof])

    # 5. Save the model
    output_file = "house_model.obj"
    house.export(output_file)

    print(f"3D House model created and saved as '{output_file}'")
    print("You can open this file in Blender, Maya, or a web viewer.")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    create_house()
```

### How to View the Model
1.  **Run the script** in your terminal or Python IDE.
2.  Once the file `house_model.obj` is generated, you can open it using:
    *   **Blender** (Free, industry standard)
    *   **MeshLab** (Free, open source)
    *   **Three.js** (If you want to embed it in a web page)

### Alternative: Web-Based 3D (HTML/JS)
If you prefer to see the result immediately in a browser without installing Python, you can use **Three.js**. Below is a single-file HTML code you can save as `house.html` and open in your browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>3D House Viewer</title>
    <style>
        body { margin: 0; overflow: hidden; }
        canvas { display: block; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Import Three.js from CDN -->
    <script type="importmap">
        {
            "imports": {
                "three": "https://unpkg.com/three@0.160.0/build/three.module.js"
            }
        }
    </script>

    <script type="module">
        import * as THREE from 'three';

        // 1. Scene Setup
        const scene = new THREE.Scene();
        scene.background = new THREE.Color(0x87CEEB); // Sky blue

        // 2. Camera
        const camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera(75, window.innerWidth / window.innerHeight, 0.1, 1000);
        camera.position.set(15, 10, 15);
        camera.lookAt(0, 0, 0);

        // 3. Renderer
        const renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer({ antialias: true });
        renderer.setSize(window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight);
        renderer.shadowMap.enabled = true;
        document.body.appendChild(renderer.domElement);

        // 4. Lighting
        const ambientLight = new THREE.AmbientLight(0xffffff, 0.6);
        scene.add(ambientLight);

        const dirLight = new THREE.DirectionalLight(0xffffff, 1);
        dirLight.position.set(10, 20, 10);
        dirLight.castShadow = true;
        scene.add(dirLight);

        // 5. Create House Geometry
        const houseGroup = new THREE.Group();

        // Materials
        const wallMaterial = new THREE.MeshStandardMaterial({ color: 0x8B4513 }); // Brown
        const roofMaterial = new THREE.MeshStandardMaterial({ color: 0x800080 }); // Purple

        // Body (Box)
        const bodyGeo = new THREE.BoxGeometry(10, 8, 10);
        const body = new THREE.Mesh(bodyGeo, wallMaterial);
        body.position.y = 4;
        body.castShadow = true;
        body.receiveShadow = true;
        houseGroup.add(body);

        // Roof (Cone)
        const roofGeo = new THREE.ConeGeometry(9, 4, 4); // 4 sides for pyramid
        const roof = new THREE.Mesh(roofGeo, roofMaterial);
        roof.position.y = 10; // On top of body
        roof.castShadow = true;
        houseGroup.add(roof);

        // Floor (Plane)
        const floorGeo = new THREE.PlaneGeometry(50, 50);
        const floorMat = new THREE.MeshStandardMaterial({ color: 0x228B22 });
        const floor = new THREE.Mesh(floorGeo, floorMat);
        floor.rotation.x = -Math.PI / 2;
        floor.receiveShadow = true;
        scene.add(floor);

        scene.add(houseGroup);

        // 6. Animation Loop
        function animate() {
            requestAnimationFrame(animate);
            houseGroup.rotation.y += 0.005; // Slowly rotate house
            renderer.render(scene, camera);
        }

        // Handle Window Resize
        window.addEventListener('resize', () => {
            camera.aspect = window.innerWidth / window.innerHeight;
            camera.updateProjectionMatrix();
            renderer.setSize(window.innerWidth, window.innerHeight);
        });

        animate();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```
